    PayloadState<T>
    A state has various important tasks it must attend to: success; when a character points to another state, it must return that state failure; when a character has no matching state, the algorithm must be able to fall back on a state with less depth emits; when this state is passed and keywords have been matched, the matches and their payloads must be 'emitted' so that they can be used later on.
    PayloadToken<T>
    PayloadToken holds a text ("the fragment") an emits some output.
    PayloadTrie<T>
    A trie implementation that carries a payload.
    PayloadTrie.PayloadTrieBuilder<T>
    Builder class to create a PayloadTrie instance.
    State
    A state has various important tasks it must attend to: success; when a character points to another state, it must return that state failure; when a character has no matching state, the algorithm must be able to fall back on a state with less depth emits; when this state is passed and keywords have been matched, the matches must be 'emitted' so that they can be used later on.
